 hubot is in\n\nFor example, if your hubot lives at myhubot.herokuapp.com, then you will set the webhook URL to: http://myhubot.herokuapp.com/hubot/github-repo-listener?room=development\n\n<strong>Make sure to use \"application/json\" as type.</strong>\n\n**SECURITY WARNING**: This script does not currently validate the Github Secret. PRs are welcome!\n\n## Local Testing\n\nYou can use ```./scripts/github_webhook_simulator.js event_name``` to emit different events. ```pull_request```, ```pull_request_closed```, ```pull_request_merged```, ```pull_request_reopened``` and ```pull_request_review_comment``` are the most useful ones.\n\n\n## Author\n\nMarek Ventur [marekventur](http://github.com/marekventur)\n\n## License\n\nMIT License; see LICENSE for further details.\n","maintainers":[{"name":"marekventur","email":"marekventur@gmail.com"}],"time":{"modified":"2017-04-18T10:54:24.963Z","created":"2017-01-27T17:09:47.597Z","1.0.0":"2017-01-27T17:09:47.597Z","1.0.1":"2017-04-18T10:54:24.963Z"},"homepage":"https://github.com/marekventur/hubot-github-slack-pr-threads#readme","keywords":["hubot","chat","slack","threads","github","pull-request","pullrequest","hubot-scripts"],"repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/marekventur/hubot-github-slack-pr-threads.git"},"author":{"name":"Marek Ventur","email":"marekventur@gmail.com"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/marekventur/hubot-github-slack-pr-threads/issues"},"license":"MIT","readmeFilename":"README.md","users":{"decoded":true}}
